sql:
SELECT latitude
FROM satellite_data
WHERE confidence > 50;

SELECT fire_id
FROM fire_events
ORDER BY fire_id;

external_knowledge:
- The term "fire events" refers to instances of fires that have been recorded and tracked; 
- "Updates" likely refer to new information or changes made to the status of these fire events; 
- "Satellite data" refers to data collected by satellites that could be relevant to the fire events, such as temperature, vegetation health, or fire spread information; 
- "Unique users" refers to distinct individuals who have accessed this satellite data.

sql:
SELECT MAX(brightness) AS max_brightness
FROM satellite_data
WHERE satellite_id = 1;

SELECT fire_id, fire_location
FROM fire_events
ORDER BY fire_id, fire_location;
